&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Patient Services Co-ordinator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Outpatients team at the Royal Surrey County Hospital are looking for staff to work with our Outpatient Reception team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Skills Required: &lt;br /&gt; - General Admin/Reception Experience &lt;br /&gt; - Good communication skills - both verbal &amp; written &lt;br /&gt; - Good telephone manner &lt;br /&gt; - Professional and polite approach to patients and staff &lt;br /&gt; - Good keyboard/PC skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should be mobile and able to move between departments. The position also requires some manual handling tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further details of the role are included in the attached job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates are required to work 30 hours a week and will need to be flexible between the hours of 8.00am - 5.30pm Monday to Friday. Shifts are a mixture of 8.00 - 4.30pm or 9.00 - 5.30pm with an hour for lunch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please contact Michaela Tyler on 01483 571122 ext. 4798&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
